SIMPLE: whatever
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whatever
<hw>What*ev"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <def>Anything soever
which; the thing or things of any kind; being this or that; of one
nature or another; one thing or another; anything that may be; all that;
the whole that; all particulars that; -- used both substantively and
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whatever</qex> fortune stays from his word.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whatever</qex> Earth, all-bearing mother, yields.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whatever</qex> be its intrinsic value.</q> <rj><qau>J. H.
Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Whatever</xex> often follows a noun, being used
elliptically. ⟦ldquo⟧There being no room for any physical discovery
<xex>whatever</xex>⟦rdquo⟧ [<it>sc.</it> it may be].</note>
<rj><au>Whately.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whatnot shelf</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Whatnot</ent>⟦br⟧
